        <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="class_memory_pool" kindref="compound">MemoryPool</ref> allocation function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>A pointer to the memory block of template type T</para>
</simplesect>
This function allocates a memory slab object by calling function k_mem_slab_alloc provided by the operating system, which return the pointer to the memory block block_ptr and a pointer to the memory slab administration structure my_slab. Afterwards allocated memory is cleared by setting the conplete content to 0. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
