    <briefdescription>
<para>RTOS wrapper for memory pool support. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The sema class implements a C++ wrapper of the Memory Slab API provided by the Zephyr operating system. See details in Zephyr <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/kernel/memory_management/slabs.html">Memory Slab documentation</ulink> or in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/apidoc/latest/group__mem__slab__apis.html">API documentation</ulink>. The sema class provides methods to allocate and free fixed size memory blocks of concretized type T. It furthermore provides a method to print out statistics. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
